<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:51PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Cherokee and southeastern Pickens Counties through 515 PM EDT...
At 451 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Tate, or near Jasper,
moving south at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, heavy rain, pea sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Jasper, Ball Ground, Nelson, Talking Rock, Marblehill, Tate and
Reavis Mountain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
